SIMPLE: projectile
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Projectile
<hw>Pro*ject"ile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>projectile</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Projecting or impelling forward; <as>as, a
<ex>projectile</ex> force</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Caused or imparted by impulse or projection;
impelled forward; <as>as, <ex>projectile</ex> motion</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Projectile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Projectile
<hw>Pro*ject"ile</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>projectile</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A body projected, or impelled forward, by force;
especially, a missile adapted to be shot from a firearm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A part of
mechanics which treats of the motion, range, time of flight, etc., of
bodies thrown or driven through the air by an impelling force.</def><--
= ballistics? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- projectile vomiting, vomiting with such force as to expel the
vomitus over a distance. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Projection</ent>⟦br⟧
